============================================================
C. CITATION POLICY (academic and research use)
============================================================

If you use this repository in academic, research, or teaching
contexts, you MUST cite both:

  1. The original FUS paper:

       D'Aniello, G., Della Corte, M., Gaeta, M.
       "A Recommendation System Based on Fuzzy Signature."
       IEEE Access, vol. 14, pp. 9975-9985, 2026.
       DOI: 10.1109/ACCESS.2026.3656087

  2. This replication:

       Ali, S., Ucar, I., Sevinc Aldogan, Y., Guidoum, Y.
       "Faithful Replication of FUS (D'Aniello et al., IEEE Access 2026)."
       University course project, 2026.
       Available at: https://github.com/SherwanAli0/Recommender-System-Paper-Replication

A machine-readable CITATION.cff is provided at the repository root,
and BibTeX entries for both citations are in the README.

Failure to cite when using this work in published academic output is
both a violation of the CC-BY 4.0 attribution requirement (Section B)
and contrary to academic integrity norms.

